MSW runtime boundary was untouched; no runtime files were edited.

4. unresolved risks

The repo already had substantial pre-existing uncommitted changes, including in the target selected-state files, so `git diff` against `HEAD` is not a clean isolation of only this turn’s edits.

I did not rerun architecture simulation/scoring, so I cannot yet verify that `economy_pressure_unbounded` is removed or narrowed, or that economy stability improved without side effects.

`data/design_graph/economy.json` is a node graph, not a numeric config surface, so the shard now exposes the knob explicitly but does not itself store the `0.258` value.

5. recommended next bottleneck

`power_curve_replacement_pressure`, unless the next scoring pass shows `economy_pressure_unbounded` still persists after this sink-pressure adjustment.
